he%20Tories%20than%20under%20former%20Tory%20prime%20minister%20John%20Major%20in%201997%20when%20the%20Tony%20Blair-led%20Labour%20left%20them%20with%20just%20165%20MPs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20latest%20results%20push%20Keir%20Starmer%20closer%20toward%20repeating%20a%20Blair-level%20result%20for%20Labour%2C%20a%20full%2027%20years%20since%20Labour's%20longest-serving%20prime%20minister%20first%20took%20office.%20In%20that%20election%2C%20Blair%20won%20418%20out%20of%20the%20available%20659%20House%20of%20Commons%20seats%2C%26quot%3B%20reads%20the%20YouGov%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20contrast%2C%20Rishi%20Sunak%20is%20now%20heading%20for%20a%20worse%20result%20than%20John%20Major's%201997%20total%20of%20165%20seats.%20The%20coming%20tidal%20wave%20projected%20by%20this%20model%20would%20sweep%20away%20several%20major%20Conservative%20figures%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20prominent%20members%20of%20Parliament%20who%20could%20lose%20their%20House%20of%20Commons%20seat%20include%20Chancellor%20Jeremy%20Hunt%2C%20science%20minister%20Michelle%20Donelan%20and%20levelling%20up%20minister%20Michael%20Gove.%20Other%20senior%20Tories%20in%20the%20precarious%20zone%20with%20the%20electorate%20include%20Commons%20leader%20Penny%20Mordaunt%20and%20former%20minister%20Jacob%20Rees-Mogg.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Liberal%20Democrats%20are%20up%20by%20one%20seat%20based%20on%20an%20earlier%20YouGov%20model%2C%20to%2049%2C%20on%20the%20path%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20parliamentary%20comeback%26quot%3B%20without%20any%20significant%20changes%20to%20their%20national%20vote%20share.%20In%20Scotland%2C%20YouGov%20now%20projects%20Labour%20to%20comfortably%20be%20the%20largest%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20headline%20results%20based%20on%20this%20MRP%20model%20would%20be%20Labour%20at%2041%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20vote%2C%20the%20Conservatives%20at%2024%20per%20cent%2C%20the%20Liberal%20Democrats%20at%2012%20per%20cent%2C%20the%20Greens%20at%207%20per%20cent%2C%20far-right%20Reform%20UK%20at%2012%20per%20cent%2C%20and%20others%20at%201%20per%20cent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYouGov%20said%20it%20interviewed%2018%2C761%20British%20adults%20from%20March%207-27%2C%20marking%20the%20latest%20survey%20to%20predict%20a%201997-style%20outcome%20for%20the%20Conservatives%20when%20the%20nation%20goes%20to%20the%20polls%2C%20which%20Sunak%20has%20indicated%20will%20be%20held%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConstituency-level%20projections%20were%20estimated%20using%20the%20same%20statistical%20method%20which%20correctly%20predicted%20the%202017%20and%202019%20UK%20general%20elections%20-%20multi-level%20modelling%20and%20post-stratification%20(MRP)%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20repeal%20of%20the%20Fixed-term%20Parliaments%20Act%20in%202022%20restored%20the%20ability%20of%20British%20prime%20ministers%20to%20set%20election%20dates.%20However%2C%20by%20law%20a%20general%20election%20has%20to%20take%20place%20at%20least%20every%20five%20years%2C%20making%20January%202025%20the%20outermost%20deadline%20for%20Sunak%20to%20go%20to%20the%20ballot%20box.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712199540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2F6om28o0g_rishi-sunak-reuters_625x300_12_January_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frishi-sunaks-conservative-party-set-for-worst-election-defeat-in-uk-shows-new-survey-5368491%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20major%20survey%20of%20over%2018%2C000%20people%20on%20Wednesday%20predicted%20a%20wipeout%20for%20British%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak-led%20governing%20Conservative%20Party%2C%20with%20the%20Opposition%20Labour%20Party%20forecast%20to%20win%