cluding%20senior%20US%20officials'%20emails%2C%20in%20a%20preventable%20attack%20last%20summer%2C%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cisa.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-04%2FCSRB_Review_of_the_Summer_2023_MEO_Intrusion_Final_508c.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereleased%20the%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Cyber%20Safety%20Review%20Board%20(CSRB)%20on%20Tuesday.%20In%20it%2C%20the%20board%20details%20a%20%26quot%3Bcascade%26quot%3B%20of%20%26quot%3Bavoidable%20errors%26quot%3B%20in%20Microsoft's%20security%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecifically%2C%20the%20board%20said%20that%20the%20hackers%20%E2%80%94%20an%20espionage%20group%20affiliated%20with%20the%20Chinese%20government%20called%20Storm-0558%20%E2%80%94%20were%20able%20to%20exploit%20several%20flaws%20in%20Microsoft's%20authentication%20system%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20sign%20in%20to%20%26quot%3Bessentially%20any%20Exchange%20Online%20account%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20Microsoft%20didn't%20adequately%20protect%20the%20signing%20keys%2C%20the%20hackers%20gained%20access%20to%20the%20email%20accounts%20of%20senior%20US%20diplomats%2C%20including%20Commerce%20Secretary%20Gina%20Raimondo%2C%20United%20States%20Ambassador%20to%20the%20People's%20Republic%20of%20China%20R.%20Nicholas%20Burns%2C%20and%20Congressman%20Don%20Bacon%2C%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20blames%20Microsoft%20for%20not%20detecting%20the%20compromised%20accounts%20on%20its%20own%20and%20only%20realizing%20something%20was%20wrong%20when%20a%20customer%20reported%20a%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Board%20finds%20that%20this%20intrusion%20was%20preventable%20and%20should%20never%20have%20occurred%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Cyber%20Safety%20Review%20Board%20wrote%20in%20its%20report.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Board%20also%20concludes%20that%20Microsoft's%20security%20culture%20was%20inadequate%20and%20requires%20an%20overhaul%2C%20particularly%20in%20light%20of%20the%20company's%20centrality%20in%20the%20technology%20ecosystem%20and%20the%20level%20of%20trust%20customers%20place%20in%20the%20company%20to%20protect%20their%20data%20and%20operations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Microsoft%20said%20%26quot%3Brecent%20events%20have%20demonstrated%20a%20need%20to%20adopt%20a%20new%20culture%20of%20engineering%20security%20in%20our%20own%20networks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20no%20organization%20is%20immune%20to%20cyberattack%20from%20well-resourced%20adversaries%2C%20we%20have%20mobilized%20our%20engineering%20teams%20to%20identify%20and%20mitigate%20legacy%20infrastructure%2C%20improve%20processes%2C%20and%20enforce%20security%20benchmarks%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Microsoft%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20board%20also%20reprimanded%20Microsoft%20for%20announcing%20in%20September%202023%20that%20it%20had%20found%20the%20root%20cause%20of%20the%20attack.%20But%20two%20months%20later%20it%20admitted%20to%20the%20board%20that%20it%20was%20wrong%20about%20the%20cause%20%E2%80%94%20and%20didn't%20update%20the%20announcement%20to%20reflect%20that%20inaccuracy%20until%20March%202024%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CSRB%20concluded%20that%20because%20Microsoft's%20systems%20are%20essential%20to%20national%20security%20and%20the%20global%20economy%2C%20the%20company%20must%20fix%20its%20security%20vulnerabilities%20quickly%20and%20substantially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-security-issues-government-report-chinese-hacks-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712177978000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660dbd481caec1275a6c9bfd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%